        { question: "How does occupancy counting support emergency planning and evacuation?", answer: "Emergency management uses real-time occupancy data to understand facility occupancy during incidents. Building managers immediately know occupancy levels in affected areas. Evacuation coordinators know how many people require evacuation from each zone. Post-evacuation, occupancy counts dropping to zero confirm complete evacuation before declaring areas clear. Historical occupancy patterns enable emergency planners to estimate occupancy during different time periods. Occupancy trends identify normally unoccupied zones where people may be unaccounted for. Integration with fire detection enables emergency systems to identify occupancy in fire-affected areas, prioritizing rescue operations. Occupancy data is critical for emergency response effectiveness and occupant safety." }
